widgets_values: Setting the optimal ControlNet preprocosser resolutions.

nodes.title: Pose
widgets_values: use pose only for humanoids, otherwise can bypass the controlnet nodes (ctrl + B)

nodes.title: Masks
widgets_values: Here we get the masks and select the ones to use for 1st pass
Use any lora you wish here

Free increase to the sampling quality, often affects the colors negatively, I've adjusted the values a bit to compensate, not mandatory but most of the time it's an improvement. Costs no sampling time!

Unless your model is specifically lcm model, lcm lora is required:
https://huggingface.co/latent-consistency/lcm-lora-sdv1-5/blob/main/pytorch_lora_weights.safetensors
Frames to skip for 1st pass. This setting entirely depends on your input video frame rate, and how many frames are initially skipped. For slow videos this can be higher.

nodes.title: IPAdapter model choice
widgets_values: You can use any 1.5 compatible IPadapter model, all of them affect the results differently.

nodes.title: Depth
widgets_values: Depth Anything is new, fast and more precise preprocessor, highly recommended. Yet I still find that the good gold "v11f1p" -depth ControlNet works best with it.

nodes.title: ControlGIF
widgets_values: This ControlNet is for referencing the source, it's trained like AnimateDiff using video and works similarly to tile or ip2p controlnets. Enable these controlnets if you have issues with tracking the source, for example rotating characters and fast movement.
Alternatively, load your own foreground/character style image here, and connect it instead

nodes.title: Preprocessors
widgets_values: Preprocessors for ControlNets are run here, previews are purely for debugging purposes.

Prompts for background generation. 

You can either use single prompt with single image, or batch for variance with same style.

Or use prompt travel, where each image in the batch has it's own style. The actual travel is done with IPAdapter

nodes.title: Masking options
widgets_values:
I've included 2 options to get the masks:

BatchCLIPSeg:
Prompt based, fast, has accuracy issues often.

Rembg:
Slow but most of the time works well. Even with animals and such subjects.

2x upscale models are good choice here for speed, but you can use whichever you want. One I used for anime style:

https://openmodeldb.info/models/2x-Higurashi-v1-compact
Interpolate back to the original frame amount
Enable this tile controlnet if you wish to have fully stable background.
1girl, 1boy, man, woman, person, human, people, nsfw
grassy meadow, sunny day, blue skies
Alternatively, load your own background style image here and connect it instead
Use only generic style prompts here, and anything you want to exaggerate
Negative prompt not going to affect anything at cfg 1.0, not important here.
red hair, green dress, masterpiece, best quality
1girl, green dress, red hair, best quality, facing camera
